{"_response_info":{"status":"ok"},"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/caesarean-section-and-driving.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/caesarean-section-and-driving","title":"Caesarean section and driving","format":"answer","details":{"need_id":"2247","business_proposition":false,"alternative_title":"","overview":"You don't need to tell the DVLA if you have had a Caesarean section","body":"\n<div class=\"summary\">\n<p>You don’t need to tell <abbr title=\"Driver Vehicle and Licensing Agency\">DVLA</abbr> if you’ve had a caesarean section.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell <abbr title=\"Driver Vehicle and Licensing Agency\">DVLA</abbr> about a medical condition that affects your driving. If you’re involved in an accident, you may be prosecuted.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Most women do not feel fit to drive for a few weeks after a caesarean, and many wait till after the 6-week check. You should stop driving after a caesarean section and only start driving again when your doctor says it&rsquo;s safe to do so. </p>\n\n<p>You should also check your motor insurance to see if there are any restrictions about driving after a caesarean section.</p>\n\n"},"updated_at":"2012-10-15T11:27:45+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Directgov","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/directgov.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":null,"type":"legacy_source"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=directgov","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/directgov"},"parent":null}],"related":[{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/driving-if-disabled.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/driving-if-disabled","title":"Medical conditions, disabilities and driving","format":"guide","details":{"need_id":"786","business_proposition":false},"updated_at":"2012-10-15T13:17:13+00:00"},{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/health-conditions-and-driving.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/health-conditions-and-driving","title":"Health conditi